  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 7 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 2 critical, 11 high, 8 medium, 18 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Luton (LTN/EGGW), Katowice Wojciech Korfanty (KTW/EPKT) and Tirana International Airport Mother Teresa (TIA/LATI); plus 10 other bases. 8 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is thunderstorm / convective risk, mist and fog / freezing fog  — most notably around Larnaca (LCA/LCLK), David the Builder Kutaisi (KUT/UGKO) and Catania-Fontanarossa (CTA/LICC). Network hotspots: Larnaca (LCA/LCLK), David the Builder Kutaisi (KUT/UGKO), Lennart Meri Tallinn (TLL/EETN), Turku (TKU/EFTU), Oslo-Gardermoen (OSL/ENGM) and 2 others. Primary drivers: thunderstorm / convective risk, mist and snow / blowing snow. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Oslo-Gardermoen (OSL/ENGM), Zvartnots (EVN/UDYZ), Sandefjord Airport, Torp (TRF/ENTO) and 9 others.",
